{"type":"message","id":"cc4a5cd0","parentId":"1b6d9304","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:20.378Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 16:10 GMT+2] UNIFIED COMMAND CENTER: REGISTRATION & LOGIC CHECK.\n\n1.  **Menu Refresh (`src/menu_refresh.py`):**\n    *   Rewrite to include ALL 13 commands.\n    *   *Emojis:* Ensure strict UTF-8 compliance.\n    *   *Descriptions:* Concise and clear.\n    *   *Execute:* Run script with `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` injected.\n\n2.  **Logic Verification (`/new`):**\n    *   *Analysis:* The `/new` command is native to OpenClaw. If we register it via `bot.set_my_commands`, Telegram will send `/new` text to the bot.\n    *   *Handling:* Ensure `src/main.py` (our bot) either *ignores* `/new` (letting OpenClaw gateway handle it if configured as pass-through) OR explicitly proxies it.\n    *   *Correct Approach:* OpenClaw Gateway intercepts `/new` automatically *before* it hits the sub-bot logic usually. But if we are running a custom bot on the same token, there might be a race.\n    *   *Resolution:* The custom bot should NOT handle `/new`. The Gateway listens for it. Registering it in the menu is UI-only, which is fine.\n\n3.  **Config Hardening:**\n    *   Verify `openclaw.json` still has `\"commands\": null`.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Confirmation of 13-button menu registration.\n    *   Verification of `/new` command behavior plan."}],"timestamp":1771164620377}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4913c7b","parentId":"cc4a5cd0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:25.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Menu Commands**\n\nI'm currently focused on the command refresh process. I plan to check for a file named `src/menu_refresh.py`. If it doesn't exist, I'll generate one. Then, I need to incorporate the thirteen specific commands into the script. This will likely involve restructuring some code.\n\n\n**Planning the Implementation**\n\nI've outlined the core steps: first, I'll address the `src/menu_refresh.py` file. I'll read its contents, or create it. Then, the thirteen commands will be integrated. Next, I'll review `src/main.py` and `openclaw.json` to prevent potential clashes or inconsistencies with the `/new` command and command structure, as this is important to ensure a working menu.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771164625699_229","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/menu_refresh.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771164625813_230","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771164625946_231","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"openclaw.json"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5132,"output":148,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5280,"cost":{"input":0.010263999999999999,"output":0.001776,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012039999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771164620378}}
{"type":"message","id":"e6992898","parentId":"b4913c7b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:25.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771164625699_229","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport sys\nimport requests\nimport json\n\n# Force UTF-8 for stdout/stderr\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\nsys.stderr.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nBOT_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\nif not BOT_TOKEN:\n    print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not found in environment variables.\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n\nAPI_URL = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{BOT_TOKEN}/setMyCommands\"\n\ncommands = [\n    {\"command\": \"start\", \"description\": \"🚀 Start the bot\"},\n    {\"command\": \"help\", \"description\": \"📚 Show help\"},\n    {\"command\": \"status\", \"description\": \"📊 System status\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_logs\", \"description\": \"📜 View DMarket logs\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_wallet\", \"description\": \"💰 Check DMarket wallet\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_panic\", \"description\": \"🚨 PANIC MODE - Stop trading\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_inspect\", \"description\": \"🔍 Inspect specific item\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_reload\", \"description\": \"🔄 Reload DMarket config\"},\n    {\"command\": \"settings\", \"description\": \"⚙️ Bot settings\"}\n]\n\ntry:\n    response = requests.post(API_URL, json={\"commands\": commands})\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    print(f\"✅ Menu commands updated successfully: {response.status_code}\")\n    print(json.dumps(response.json(), indent=2))\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"❌ Failed to update commands: {e}\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771164625977}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4eb4435","parentId":"e6992898","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:25.983Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771164625813_230","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\nfrom telegram import Update, BotCommand\nfrom telegram.ext import ApplicationBuilder, ContextTypes, CommandHandler\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    level=logging.INFO\n)\n\n# Paths (Assuming run from workspace root)\nAGENT_WRAPPER = \"src/agent_wrapper.py\"\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nMASTER_PROTOCOL = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nEVOLUTION_LOG = \"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md\"\n\n# Token from Env\nTOKEN = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n\nasync def dm_start(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🚀 Start DMarket HFT (High-Frequency)\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🚀 Starting DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        # Run agent_wrapper from root\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/start_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        # Format output\n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to start bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_stop(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🛑 Stopping DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/stop_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to stop bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    # Fleet Status\n    fleet_apps = [\"730\", \"570\", \"440\", \"252490\"]\n    active_count = 0\n    for app_id in fleet_apps:\n        if os.path.exists(f\"src/bot_{app_id}.pid\"):\n            active_count += 1\n            \n    # Security Status (Check if critical folders exist)\n    sec_active = os.path.exists(\"D:/Dmarket_bot/specs\") and os.path.exists(\"D:/Dmarket_bot/memory/checkpoints\")\n    sec_text = \"Active\" if sec_active else \"Warning\"\n\n    status_msg = (\n        f\"✅ Fleet: {active_count} Active\\n\"\n        f\"✅ Security: {sec_text}\\n\"\n        f\"⏳ Profit: Calculating...\"\n    )\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg)\n\nasync def dm_dashboard(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📈 Open Control Panel\"\"\"\n    # Assuming local streamlit or configured URL\n    url = os.getenv(\"STREAMLIT_URL\", \"http://localhost:8501\")\n    await update.message.reply_text(f\"📈 **Control Panel:** [Open Dashboard]({url})\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def dm_compact(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🗜 Compact Database\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🗜 Compacting database resources...\")\n    # Placeholder for actual maintenance logic\n    await asyncio.sleep(2)\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"✅ Database compacted successfully.\")\n\nasync def post_init(application):\n    \"\"\"Set up commands on bot startup\"\"\"\n    commands = [\n        BotCommand(\"dm_start\", \"🚀 Start DMarket HFT\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_stop\", \"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_status\", \"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_dashboard\", \"📈 Open Control Panel\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_compact\", \"🗜 Compact Database\"),\n    ]\n    await application.bot.delete_my_commands()\n    await application.bot.set_my_commands(commands)\n    logging.info(\"Commands registered with Telegram.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    if not TOKEN:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not set. Please set it in your environment.\")\n        # For testing purposes, we might want to exit gracefully or mock it, \n        # but for a real deployment, we exit.\n        sys.exit(1)\n        \n    application = ApplicationBuilder().token(TOKEN).post_init(post_init).build()\n    \n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_start', dm_start))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_stop', dm_stop))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_status', dm_status))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_dashboard', dm_dashboard))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_compact', dm_compact))\n    \n    print(\"Telegram Bot Control Interface Started.\")\n    application.run_polling()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771164625982}}
{"type":"message","id":"661a331c","parentId":"a4eb4435","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:25.988Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771164625946_231","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"fleet_mode\": true,\n  \"commands\": null,\n  \"env\": {\n    \"FLEET_GAMES\": \"730,570,440,252490\"\n  },\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"version\": \"2.0.0\",\n    \"last_update\": \"2026-02-15\",\n    \"active_skills\": [\n      \"grep-master\",\n      \"bat-cat\",\n      \"self-improving-agent\",\n      \"random-forest-predictor\",\n      \"websockets-stable\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"system_capabilities\": {\n    \"batch_execution\": true,\n    \"lazy_loading\": true,\n    \"checkpoints\": true,\n    \"Ed25519\": true\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771164625987}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c23ef60","parentId":"661a331c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:10:44.306Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining Code Structure**\n\nI'm currently reviewing `src/menu_refresh.py`, `src/main.py`, and `openclaw.json`. I've determined that `menu_refresh.py` directly calls the Telegram API with `requests` and implements 9 commands. However, it's notably missing crucial error handling and other features.\n\n\n**Assessing Command Overlap**\n\nI've examined `src/main.py` more closely. It uses `python-telegram-bot` and defines five commands that would overwrite the menu if active. Thankfully, it's missing `/new`. I'm now drafting a detailed command list, ensuring that when I rewrite `src/menu_refresh.py`, it includes all 13 necessary commands, integrating standard OpenClaw features and requested DMarket additions.\n\n\n**Formulating the Command Set**\n\nNow, I'm focusing on the implementation details for `src/menu_refresh.py`. I've finalized the command list, integrating OpenClaw's core functionality with the custom DMarket requests. The next step is to integrate a robust logging system, and comprehensive error handling. After that, I will modify `src/main.py` accordingly.\n\n\n**Analyzing Script Dependencies**\n\nI've confirmed that the custom bot in `src/main.py` will not conflict with the intended command structure. I'll remove the command reset in the `post_init` section. I'll then move on to adding the 13 unified commands to `src/menu_refresh.py`, ensuring each one's functionality is correct.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Command Set**\n\nI've reviewed the bot's functionality and resolved any command conflicts. Now I'm preparing to rewrite `src/menu_refresh.py`. I've constructed a definitive 13-command list, integrating standard OpenClaw commands and custom DMarket functions. The next step is the actual coding.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771164644071_232","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport sys\nimport requests\nimport json\n\n# Force UTF-8 for stdout/stderr\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\nsys.stderr.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nBOT_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\nif not BOT_TOKEN:\n    print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not found in environment variables.\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n\nAPI_URL = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{BOT_TOKEN}/setMyCommands\"\n\n# Unified 13-Command Menu\ncommands = [\n    {\"command\": \"start\", \"description\": \"🚀 Activate System\"},\n    {\"command\": \"new\", \"description\": \"🆕 New Session\"},\n    {\"command\": \"status\", \"description\": \"📊 System Health\"},\n    {\"command\": \"help\", \"description\": \"📚 Documentation\"},\n    {\"command\": \"settings\", \"description\": \"⚙️ Configuration\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_start\", \"description\": \"⚡ Auto-Trade ON\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_stop\", \"description\": \"🛑 Auto-Trade OFF\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_status\", \"description\": \"📈 Trade Metrics\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_wallet\", \"description\": \"💰 Balance Check\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_logs\", \"description\": \"📜 Live Logs\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_inspect\", \"description\": \"🔍 Item Analysis\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_panic\", \"description\": \"🚨 KILL SWITCH\"},\n    {\"command\": \"dm_reload\", \"description\": \"🔄 Reload Config\"}\n]\n\ntry:\n    print(f\"📡 Registering {len(commands)} commands with Telegram...\")\n    response = requests.post(API_URL, json={\"commands\": commands})\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    print(f\"✅ Menu commands updated successfully: {response.status_code}\")\n    print(json.dumps(response.json(), indent=2))\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"❌ Failed to update commands: {e}\")\n    if hasattr(e, 'response') and e.response is not None:\n         print(f\"Response: {e.response.text}\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n","file_path":"src/menu_refresh.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771164644176_233","name"